2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper proposes a method for identifying hierarchies in directed graphs, which can be applied in software engineering for analyzing dependencies between software components. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a score function for identifying hierarchies in directed graphs, which involves optimizing a partition of nodes. This is a problem in data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the detectability of ranking hierarchies in directed networks, which is a problem in systems and control. 
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes an ensemble of random graphs for investigating the detectability of ranking hierarchies, which can be seen as a machine learning problem.
